My Paper Heart is the debut album from Christian pop rock singer Francesca Battistelli, released on July 22, 2008. The album's lead single, &quot;I'm Letting Go&quot;, was released before the album in mid-2008, and was the 16th most-played song on Christian radio of 2008. The second single, &quot;Free to Be Me&quot;, was released in the beginning of January 2009, and stayed at #1 on Christian contemporary hit radio charts for seven consecutive weeks. The album hit #182 on the Billboard 200 in March 2009 and peaked at #35 in August 2010; it has sold over 100,000 copies on United States. The third single from the album, &quot;It's Your Life&quot;, is peaking at #12 on the Hot Christian Songs chart.

Francesca Battistelli (born May 18, 1985) is a Christian musician from New York City, New York. She was originally an independent artist and had released an independent album, Just a Breath, in 2004. Her first studio album on Fervent Records, My Paper Heart, was released on July 22, 2008. Her first single, &quot;I'm Letting Go&quot;, was released to radio stations in spring of 2008 and has charted on national Christian CHR charts since then. The song was the 16th most played song of 2008 on Christian radio stations according to R&amp;R magazine. Francesca Battistelli has received her first Grammy Award 2009 nomination for &quot;Best Gospel Performance&quot; with her single Free To Be Me.

